 "narr": {
  "Aqua HK": "Users eased to 3,055 in W22 and GA4 bookings slipped to 166 (\u221213% YoY), so the recovery of W21 gave way to a softer July-changeover week. Conversion rate held at 5.4% \u2014 the decline was traffic-led. Google remains the productive paid channel (CPA HK$152, just over target) while Meta CPA stays very high at HK$771.",
  "Hutong HK": "Hutong keeps outperforming: 242 GA4 bookings in W22, well up YoY, on a conversion rate that jumped to 11.0% even as users fell to 2,205. Google CPA rose to HK$434 on thin volume (11 bookings) but Meta held around HK$384. Walk-in signals remain strong.",
  "The Chinese Library": "ChinLib gave back its W21 spike: users rose to 1,654 but conversion rate dropped to 4.5%, pulling bookings to 74 (\u221220% YoY). Google is efficient (HK$137, 26 bookings) but Meta CPA is extreme at HK$2,325 on just 3 schedules \u2014 an efficiency review is warranted.",
  "Cantina": "Cantina stays well ahead of last year: 75 bookings in W22 (+63% YoY) on users up sharply to 2,053, though conversion rate is low at 3.7%. Meta improved to HK$405 CPA (13 schedules); Google CPA HK$244 on 19 bookings. Walk-in signals are strongly up YoY.",
  "Dim Sum Library": "DSL normalised from its W21 conversion peak: users flat at 1,019, conversion rate 12.4%, bookings 126 (\u221211% YoY). Google is exceptionally efficient at HK$20 CPA (53 bookings) \u2014 disproportionately high vs GA4 bookings and worth a SevenRooms cross-check. Meta is a minor channel.",
  "Shiro Pacific Place": "Pacific Place bookings eased to 70 in W22 with conversion rate at 3.7% on 1,914 users. The shared Shiro ad panels show Google at HK$100 CPA (41 bookings) and a high Meta CPA of HK$914 on 4 schedules.",
  "Shiro Central": "Shiro Central (Tai Kwun) continues its 2026 ramp: 31 GA4 bookings on 1,973 users (conversion rate 1.6%, early-stage). This is a new venue with no like-for-like last year. Ad panels are shared across the combined Shiro property."
 },
